#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:4
msgid "cmake-instrumentation(7)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:9
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:13
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:15
msgid ""
"The CMake Instrumentation API allows for the collection of timing data, "
"target information and system diagnostic information during the configure, "
"generate, build, test and install steps for a CMake project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:19
msgid ""
"All interactions with the CMake instrumentation API must specify both an API "
"version and a Data version. At this time, there is only one version for each "
"of these: see the `API v1`_ and `Data Version`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:25
msgid ""
"This feature is only available for projects using the :ref:`Makefile "
"Generators`, :ref:`Ninja Generators` or :generator:`FASTBuild`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:29
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:31
msgid ""
"CMake Instrumentation works in 2 major stages: `Data Collection`_, and "
"`Indexing`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:34
msgid ""
"`Data Collection`_ is the process by which CMake writes out instrumentation "
"data into a project build tree. The commands instrumented in this way range "
"from overall builds, to individual compile commands. The full list of "
"commands instrumented is documented under the `v1 Snippet File`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:39
msgid ""
"Collected data will accumulate until `Indexing`_ occurs: the process of "
"collating the generated data. Indexing occurs on events called \"hooks\", "
"which can be configured as part of the `v1 Query Files`_. A `v1 Index File`_ "
"is created and passed to any user-defined `Callbacks`_ provided to process "
"the data. Once all `Callbacks`_ have run, CMake deletes the files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:45
msgid ""
"Without the need for any custom `Callbacks`_, CMake can submit "
"instrumentation data to `CDash`_, or generate a `Google Trace File`_ for "
"visualization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:49
msgid "Data Collection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:51
msgid ""
"Whenever a command is executed with instrumentation enabled, a `v1 Snippet "
"File`_ is created in the project build tree with data specific to that "
"command. These files remain until after `Indexing`_ occurs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:55
msgid ""
"CMake sets the :prop_gbl:`RULE_LAUNCH_COMPILE`, :prop_gbl:`RULE_LAUNCH_LINK` "
"and :prop_gbl:`RULE_LAUNCH_CUSTOM` global properties to wrap each compile, "
"link and custom command invocation in a launcher that performs "
"instrumentation and writes out a `v1 Snippet File`_. If the project has been "
"configured with :module:`CTestUseLaunchers`, the launcher will collect "
"instrumentation data in addition to performing the communication typically "
"handled by that module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:65
msgid "Indexing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:67
msgid ""
"Indexing is the process of collating generated instrumentation data. The "
"available hooks to trigger indexing include options such as after every "
"build, or every :manual:`ctest <ctest(1)>` invocation, and are configured as "
"part of the `v1 Query Files`_. Whenever a hook is triggered, an index file "
"is generated containing a list of snippet files newer than the previous "
"indexing. This index file is passed to user-defined `Callbacks`_ commands to "
"process the data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:74
msgid ""
"Indexing and can also be performed by manually invoking :option:`ctest --"
"collect-instrumentation`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:77
msgid ""
"Indexing, and the subsequent callbacks, will not occur concurrently in a "
"single build tree. When multiple hooks trigger indexing at the same time, a "
"file-based lock is used to ensure one indexing completes, executes all of "
"its callbacks, and deletes the instrumentation data before the next indexing "
"can begin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:86
msgid "Callbacks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:88
msgid ""
"As part of the `v1 Query Files`_, users can provide a list of callbacks "
"intended to handle data collected by this feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:91
msgid ""
"Whenever `Indexing`_ occurs, each provided callback is executed, passing the "
"path to the generated `v1 Index File`_ as an additional argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:94
msgid ""
"These callbacks, defined either at the user-level or project-level, should "
"read the instrumentation data and perform any desired handling of it. The "
"index file and its listed snippets are automatically deleted by CMake once "
"all callbacks have completed. Note that a callback should never move or "
"delete these data files manually as they may be needed by other callbacks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:100
msgid ""
"If indexing is triggered again before `Callbacks`_ have finished running, "
"the generated index file will contain only instrumentation data generated "
"since the previous indexing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:105
msgid "Enabling Instrumentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:107
msgid ""
"Instrumentation can be enabled either for an individual CMake project, or "
"for all CMake projects configured and built by a user. In all cases, a "
"\"query\" represents a request for instrumentation behavior. See the `v1 "
"Query Files`_ for details on configuring this feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:113
msgid "Enabling Instrumentation at the Project-Level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:115
msgid ""
"Project code can contain instrumentation queries by using the :command:"
"`cmake_instrumentation` command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:118
msgid ""
"In addition, query files can be placed manually under ``<build>/.cmake/"
"instrumentation/<version>/query/`` at the top of a build tree. This version "
"of CMake supports only one version schema, `API v1`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:123
msgid "Enabling Instrumentation at the User-Level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:125
msgid ""
"Instrumentation can be configured at the user-level by placing query files "
"in the :envvar:`CMAKE_CONFIG_DIR` under ``<config_dir>/instrumentation/"
"<version>/query/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:132
msgid "Enabling Instrumentation for CDash Submissions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:134
msgid ""
"You can enable instrumentation when using :module:`CTest` in :ref:`Dashboard "
"Client` mode by setting the :envvar:`CTEST_USE_INSTRUMENTATION` environment "
"variable. Doing so automatically enables the ``dynamicSystemInformation`` "
"option."
msgstr ""

