#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:158
msgid ""
"By default the command line reported to CDash is truncated at the first "
"space. You can instead choose to report the full command line (including "
"arguments) by setting :envvar:`CTEST_USE_VERBOSE_INSTRUMENTATION` to 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:162
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can use the `v1 Query Files`_ to enable instrumentation "
"for CDash using the ``cdashSubmit`` and ``cdashVerbose`` options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:165
msgid ""
"In order for the submitted ``Build.xml`` file to group the snippet files "
"correctly, all configure and build commands should be executed with CTest in "
"Dashboard Client mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:172
msgid "API v1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:174
msgid ""
"The API version specifies the layout of the instrumentation directory, as "
"well as the general format of the query files and :command:"
"`cmake_instrumentation` command arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:178
msgid ""
"The Instrumentation API v1 is housed  in the ``instrumentation/v1/`` "
"directory under either ``<build>/.cmake/`` for output data and project-level "
"queries, or ``<config_dir>/`` for user-level queries. The ``v1`` component "
"of this directory is what signifies the API version. It has the following "
"subdirectories:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:184
msgid "``query/``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:185
msgid ""
"Holds query files written by users or clients. Any file with the ``.json`` "
"file extension will be recognized as a query file. These files are owned by "
"whichever client or user creates them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:189
msgid "``query/generated/``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:190
msgid ""
"Holds query files generated by a CMake project with the :command:"
"`cmake_instrumentation` command or the :envvar:`CTEST_USE_INSTRUMENTATION` "
"variable. These files are owned by CMake and are deleted and regenerated "
"automatically during the CMake configure step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:196
msgid "``data/``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:197
msgid ""
"Holds instrumentation data collected on the project. CMake owns all data "
"files, they should never be removed by other processes. Data collected here "
"remains until after `Indexing`_ occurs and all `Callbacks`_ are executed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:201
msgid "``data/index/``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:202
msgid ""
"A subset of the collected data, containing any `v1 Index Files <v1 Index "
"File_>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:205
msgid "``data/content/``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:206
msgid ""
"A subset of the collected data, containing any `v1 CMake Content Files <v1 "
"CMake Content File_>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:209
msgid "``data/trace/``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:210
msgid ""
"A subset of the collected data, containing the `Google Trace File`_ created "
"from the most recent `Indexing`_. Unlike other data files, the most recent "
"trace file remains even after `Indexing`_ occurs and all `Callbacks`_ are "
"executed, until the next time `Indexing`_ occurs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:215
msgid "``cdash/``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:216
msgid ""
"Holds temporary files used internally to generate XML content to be "
"submitted to CDash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:222
msgid "Data Version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:224
msgid ""
"The data version specifies the contents of the output files generated by the "
"`API v1`_ as part of the `Data Collection`_ and `Indexing`_ processes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:227
msgid ""
"`v1 Query Files`_, or a :command:`cmake_instrumentation` invocation, should "
"request a specific Data Version, and `v1 Data Files`_ of the corresponding "
"version will be generated and sent to the user `Callbacks`_ defined in that "
"query."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:232
msgid ""
"Currently, the only supported version is ``1``. A new version number will be "
"created whenever previously included data is removed or reformatted such "
"that scripts written to parse this data may become incompatible with the new "
"format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:239
msgid "v1 Query Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:241
msgid ""
"Any file with the ``.json`` extension under the ``instrumentation/v1/query/"
"`` directory is recognized as a query for instrumentation data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:244
msgid ""
"These files must contain a JSON object with the following keys. The "
"``version`` key is required, but all other fields are optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:247
#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:404
#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:540
msgid "``version``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:248
msgid ""
"The `Data Version`_ of snippet file to generate, an integer. Currently the "
"only supported version is ``1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:251
msgid "``callbacks``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:252
msgid ""
"A list of command-line strings for `Callbacks`_ to handle collected "
"instrumentation data. Whenever these callbacks are executed, the full path "
"to a `v1 Index File`_ is appended to the arguments included in the string."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:256
msgid "``hooks``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:257
msgid ""
"A list of strings specifying when `Indexing`_ should occur automatically. "
"These are the intervals when instrumentation data should be collated and "
"user `Callbacks`_ should be invoked to handle the data. Elements in this "
"list should be one of the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:262
msgid "``postGenerate``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:263
msgid "``preBuild`` (called when ``ninja``  or ``make`` is invoked)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:264
msgid "``postBuild`` (called when ``ninja`` or ``make`` completes)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:265
msgid "``preCMakeBuild`` (called when :option:`cmake --build` is invoked)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:266
msgid "``postCMakeBuild`` (called when :option:`cmake --build` completes)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:267
msgid "``postCMakeInstall``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:268
msgid "``postCMakeWorkflow``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:269
msgid "``postCTest``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:271
msgid ""
"``preBuild`` and ``postBuild`` are not supported when using the :generator:"
"`MSYS Makefiles` or :generator:`FASTBuild` generators. Additionally, they "
"will not be triggered when the build tool is invoked by :option:`cmake --"
"build`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:276
msgid "``options``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:277
msgid ""
"A list of strings used to enable certain optional behavior, including the "
"collection of certain additional data. Elements in this list should be one "
"of the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:281
#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:574
msgid "``staticSystemInformation``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:282
msgid ""
"Enables collection of the static information about the host machine CMake is "
"being run from. This data is collected during `Indexing`_ and is included in "
"the generated `v1 Index File`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:286
#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:473
msgid "``dynamicSystemInformation``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:287
msgid ""
"Enables collection of the dynamic information about the host machine CMake "
"is being run from. Data is collected for every `v1 Snippet File`_ generated "
"by CMake, and includes information from immediately before and after the "
"command is executed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:292
msgid "``cdashSubmit``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:293
msgid ""
"Enables including instrumentation data in CDash. This is equivalent to "
"having the :envvar:`CTEST_USE_INSTRUMENTATION` environment variable enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:297
msgid "``cdashVerbose``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:298
msgid ""
"Enables including the full untruncated commands in data submitted to CDash. "
"Equivalent to having the :envvar:`CTEST_USE_VERBOSE_INSTRUMENTATION` and :"
"envvar:`CTEST_USE_INSTRUMENTATION` environment variables enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:303
#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:569
msgid "``trace``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:304
msgid ""
"Enables generation of a `Google Trace File`_ during `Indexing`_ to visualize "
"data from the `v1 Snippet Files <v1 Snippet File_>`_ collected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:307
msgid ""
"The ``callbacks`` listed will be invoked during the specified hooks *at a "
"minimum*. When there are multiple query files, the ``callbacks``, ``hooks`` "
"and ``options`` between them will be merged. Therefore, if any query file "
"includes any ``hooks``, every ``callback`` across all query files will be "
"executed at every ``hook`` across all query files. Additionally, if any "
"query file requests optional data using the ``options`` field, any related "
"data will be present in all snippet files. User written ``callbacks`` should "
"be able to handle the presence of this optional data, since it may be "
"requested by an unrelated query."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:317
msgid ""
"The JSON format is described in machine-readable form by :download:`this "
"JSON schema </manual/instrumentation/query-v1-schema.json>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:320
#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:505
#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:602
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:322
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"version\": 1,\n"
"  \"callbacks\": [\n"
"    \"/usr/bin/python callback.py\",\n"
"    \"/usr/bin/cmake -P callback.cmake arg\",\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"hooks\": [\n"
"    \"postCMakeBuild\",\n"
"    \"postCMakeInstall\"\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"options\": [\n"
"    \"staticSystemInformation\",\n"
"    \"dynamicSystemInformation\",\n"
"    \"cdashSubmit\",\n"
"    \"trace\"\n"
"  ]\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:342
msgid ""
"In this example, after every :option:`cmake --build` or :option:`cmake --"
"install` invocation, an index file ``index-<timestamp>.json`` will be "
"generated in ``<build>/.cmake/instrumentation/v1/data/index`` containing a "
"list of data snippet files created since the previous indexing. The commands "
"``/usr/bin/python callback.py index-<timestamp>.json`` and ``/usr/bin/cmake -"
"P callback.cmake arg index-<timestamp>.json`` will be executed in that "
"order. The index file will contain the ``staticSystemInformation`` data and "
"each snippet file listed in the index will contain the "
"``dynamicSystemInformation`` data. Additionally, the index file will contain "
"the path to the generated `Google Trace File`_. Once both callbacks have "
"completed, the index file and data files listed by it (including snippet "
"files, but not the trace file) will be deleted from the project build tree. "
"The instrumentation data will be present in the XML files submitted to "
"CDash, but with truncated command strings because ``cdashVerbose`` was not "
"enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:359
msgid "v1 Data Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:361
msgid ""
"There are four types of data files generated as part of `API v1`_: the `v1 "
"Snippet File`_, `v1 Index File`_, `v1 CMake Content File`_, and the `Google "
"Trace File`_. These files live in ``<build>/.cmake/instrumentation/v1/data/"
"`` under the project build tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:366
msgid ""
"Note that the ``v1`` delineation of these files refers to the `API v1`_. The "
"`Data Version`_ of these files is specified with a ``version`` field as part "
"of the file contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:374
msgid "v1 Snippet File"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:376
msgid ""
"Snippet files are generated for every compile, link and custom command "
"invoked as part of the CMake build or install step and contain "
"instrumentation data about the command executed. Additionally, snippet files "
"are created for the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:381
msgid "The CMake configure step"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:382
msgid "The CMake generate step"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:383
msgid "Entire build step (executed with :option:`cmake --build`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:384
msgid "Entire install step (executed with :option:`cmake --install`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:385
msgid ""
"Each time :manual:`ctest <ctest(1)>` is invoked to :ref:`run tests <Run "
"Tests>` (even if no tests are found)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:387
msgid "Each individual test executed by :manual:`ctest <ctest(1)>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:389
msgid ""
"These files remain in the build tree until after `Indexing`_ occurs and any "
"user-specified `Callbacks`_ are executed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:394
msgid ""
"Configure and generate snippet files are not written by CMake until the "
"generate step is complete. When using :manual:`cmake-gui(1)` or :manual:"
"`ccmake(1)`, triggering only configure step(s) without generating the "
"project files will not generate any configure snippets. Once the generate "
"step is run, there will be one configure snippet for each time the configure "
"step was run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:401
msgid ""
"Snippet files have a filename with the syntax ``<role>-<hash>-<timestamp>."
"json`` and contain the following data:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:405
msgid ""
"The `Data Version`_ of the snippet file, an integer. Currently the version "
"is always ``1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:408
msgid "``command``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:409
msgid "The full command executed. Excluded when ``role`` is ``build``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:411
msgid "``workingDir``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:412
msgid "The working directory in which the ``command`` was executed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:414
msgid "``result``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:415
msgid ""
"The exit code of the command, an integer. This will be ``null`` when "
"``role`` is ``build``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:418
msgid "``role``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:419
msgid ""
"The type of command executed, which will be one of the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:421
msgid "``configure``: the CMake configure step"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:422
msgid "``generate``: the CMake generate step"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:423
msgid "``compile``: an individual compile step invoked during the build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:424
msgid "``link``: an individual link step invoked during the build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:425
msgid "``custom``: an individual custom command invoked during the build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:426
msgid ""
"``build``: a complete ``make`` or ``ninja`` invocation (not through :option:"
"`cmake --build`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:428
msgid "``cmakeBuild``: a complete :option:`cmake --build` invocation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:429
msgid "``cmakeInstall``: a complete :option:`cmake --install` invocation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:430
msgid "``install``: an individual ``cmake -P cmake_install.cmake`` invocation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:431
msgid "``ctest``: a complete :manual:`ctest <ctest(1)>` command invocation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:432
msgid "``test``: a single test executed by :manual:`ctest <ctest(1)>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:434
msgid "``target``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:435
msgid ""
"The CMake target associated with the command. Only included when ``role`` is "
"``compile`` or ``link``, or when ``role`` is ``custom`` and the custom "
"command is attached to a target with :command:`add_custom_command(TARGET)`. "
"In conjunction with ``cmakeContent``, this can be used to look up the "
"target :prop_tgt:`TYPE` and :prop_tgt:`LABELS`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:441
msgid "``timeStart``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:442
msgid ""
"Time at which the command started, expressed as the number of milliseconds "
"since the system epoch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:445
msgid "``duration``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:446
msgid "The duration that the command ran for, expressed in milliseconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:448
msgid "``outputs``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:449
msgid ""
"The command's output file(s), an array. Only included when ``role`` is one "
"of: ``compile``, ``link``, ``custom``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:452
msgid "``outputSizes``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:453
msgid ""
"The size(s) in bytes of the ``outputs``, an array. For files which do not "
"exist, the size is 0. Included under the same conditions as the ``outputs`` "
"field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:457
msgid "``source``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:458
msgid ""
"The source file being compiled. Only included when ``role`` is ``compile``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:460
msgid "``language``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:461
msgid ""
"The language of the source file being compiled. Only included when ``role`` "
"is ``compile`` or ``link``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:464
msgid "``testName``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:465
msgid ""
"The name of the test being executed. Only included when ``role`` is ``test``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:468
msgid "``config``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:469
msgid ""
"The :ref:`Build Configuration <Build Configurations>`, such as ``Release`` "
"or ``Debug``. Only included when ``role`` is one of: ``compile``, ``link``, "
"``custom``, ``install``, ``test``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:474
msgid ""
"Specifies the dynamic information collected about the host machine CMake is "
"being run from. Data is collected for every snippet file generated by CMake, "
"with data immediately before and after the command is executed. Only "
"included when enabled by the `v1 Query Files`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:479
msgid "``beforeHostMemoryUsed``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:480
msgid "The Host Memory Used in KiB at ``timeStart``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:482
msgid "``afterHostMemoryUsed``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:483
msgid "The Host Memory Used in KiB at ``timeStart + duration``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:485
msgid "``beforeCPULoadAverage``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:486
msgid ""
"The Average CPU Load at ``timeStart``, or ``null`` if it cannot be "
"determined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:489
msgid "``afterCPULoadAverage``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:490
msgid ""
"The Average CPU Load at ``timeStart + duration``, or ``null`` if it cannot "
"be determined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:493
msgid "``cmakeContent``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:494
msgid ""
"The path to a `v1 CMake Content File`_ located under ``data``, which "
"contains information about the CMake configure and generate steps "
"responsible for generating the ``command`` in this snippet. When using :"
"manual:`cmake-gui(1)` or :manual:`ccmake(1)`, this field may be ``null`` for "
"all configure steps up to the most recent one before the generate step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:500
msgid "``showOnly``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:501
msgid ""
"A boolean representing whether the :option:`--show-only <ctest --show-only>` "
"option was passed to :manual:`ctest <ctest(1)>`. Only included when ``role`` "
"is ``ctest``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-instrumentation.7.rst:507
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"version\": 1,\n"
"  \"command\" : \"\\\"/usr/bin/c++\\\" \\\"-MD\\\" \\\"-MT\\\" \\"
"\"CMakeFiles/main.dir/main.cxx.o\\\" \\\"-MF\\\" \\\"CMakeFiles/main.dir/"
"main.cxx.o.d\\\" \\\"-o\\\" \\\"CMakeFiles/main.dir/main.cxx.o\\\" \\\"-c\\"
